    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 2. DC motor\n\nArmature current $i_a$, angular speed $\\omega$. Input: armature voltage $v_a$. Output: speed.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "m_motor : mod_load(\"../DCMotor.mo\")$\nmod_print(m_motor)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 7,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Model:  DCMotor\n  parameters:  [[Ra,1.0],[La,0.01],[Kt,0.05],[Ke,0.05],[Jm,0.001],[Bv,1.0e-4]]\n  states:      [ia,omega]\n  derivs:      [der_ia,der_omega]\n  inputs:      [va]\n  outputs:     [y]\n  initial:     [[ia,0],[omega,0]]\n  residuals:\n     -va+Ke*omega+Ra*ia+La*der_ia  = 0\n     Bv*omega-Kt*ia+Jm*der_omega  = 0\n     y-omega  = 0"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "[Am, Bm, Cm, Dm] : mod_state_space(m_motor, [ia = 0, omega = 0, va = 0])$\nprint(\"DC motor A =\")$ Am;\nprint(\"DC motor B =\")$ Bm;",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 8,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "DC motor A =\nmatrix([-100.0,-5.0],[50.0,-0.1])\nDC motor B ="
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi 100.0\\cr 0.0\\cr\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 8,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "The DC motor has one fast pole (electrical, $\\sim -100$ rad/s) and one slow pole\n(mechanical) \u2014 the response shows both timescales.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
